cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the segmentation of left ventricle myocardium in cardiac cine MR images using deep learning techniques. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach is based on recurrent neural networks (RNN), specifically a multi-level convolutional long short-term memory (ConvLSTM) model, which involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could be classified under multimedia (cs.MM).
